Package: PREDICTbreastML
Type: Package
Title: REDICT breast-ML: An equity-centered machine learning model for individualized breast cancer prognosis in the US population
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Yi-Wen Hsiao [aut],
    Paul D. P. Pharoah [aut],
    Pei-Chen Peng [aut]
Maintainer: Yi-Wen Hsiao <yi-wen.hsiao@cshs.org>
Description: PREDICTbreastML implements an updated machine-learning version of the PREDICT breast cancer prognostic framework. Trained and validated on the largest and most diverse SEER cohort, the package applies population reweighting, treatment-effect modeling, and modern survival-learning methods to improve accuracy and fairness. It uses key demographic, tumor, and treatment variables to estimate breast cancerâ€“specific, other-cause, and all-cause mortality. The package also provides individualized estimates of chemotherapy benefit. PREDICTbreastML offers a robust and reproducible tool for breast cancer risk prediction and treatment decision support.
